      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesnt feel temporary though. it’s not just stress. it feels like the core of me is just... gone. like i'm just carrying around this heavy, old weight of a body that doesn't even belong to me anymore. it’s exhausting pretending to be someone who actually has a life to live.",
